<exercise id="fs-id3107170" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1563556">
    <para id="import-auto-id3204311">An infant’s pulse rate is measured to be <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>130</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">±</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"130" +- 5} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> beats/min. What is the percent uncertainty in this measurement?</para>
</problem></exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1359647" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1487162">
    <para id="import-auto-id1341946">(a) Suppose that a person has an average heart rate of 72.0 beats/min. How many beats does he or she have in 2.0 y? (b) In 2.00 y? (c) In 2.000 y?</para>
</problem>    
<solution id="fs-id1671653">
    
    <para id="import-auto-id3142483">(a) <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mn>6</m:mn>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mtext>10</m:mtext>
                      
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                      
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mtext> beats</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{7 "." 6 times "10" rSup { size 8{7} } " beats"} {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math> 
    </para><para id="import-auto-id941468">(b) <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mtext>57</m:mtext>
                    <m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo>
                    <m:msup>
                      <m:mtext>10</m:mtext>
                      
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                      
                    </m:msup>
                  </m:mrow>
                  <m:mtext> beats</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:mrow>
            
